sec.p:
The largest difference, from the meta-analysis, between demographic categories and social support is seen in employment status and religious service attendance (see Tables 3 and 4). Employment status varies from a mean level of social support for the unemployed of 6.82 (95% CI: 6.37, 7.26) to a mean level for students of 7.61 (95% CI: 7.27, 7.96) (p < 0.001). Religious service attendance varies from a mean for those who never attend of 7.10 (95% CI: 6.67, 7.53) to a mean for those who attend more than once a week of 7.82 (95% CI: 7.42, 8.21) (p < 0.001).
